hlibc

DESCRIPTION:
------------

	hlibc is an experimental libc targeted at the linux kernel's syscall
	ABI. It is a standalone libc which supports the i386, x86_64, arm and
	aarch64 architectures.

	hlibc is a freestanding implementation with a subset of the POSIX, C99
	and C11 hosted implementation requirements. The mathematics library is
	a minimalistic fork of Sun fdlibm focused on IEEE-754-2008 floating
	point research and the study of fdlibm's core components.


BUILDING:
---------

	hlibc contains creates a wrapper for gcc or clang that redirects the
	compiler's linking options ergo allowing hlibc to be installed and
	used without root privilege.

		git clone https://git.hlibc.xyz/lab/hlibc
		cd hlibc

	Instructions for gcc:
		CC=gcc ./configure --prefix=/home/$USER/buildarea 
		CC=gcc make && make install
		/home/$USER/buildarea/bin/gcc-wrap hello.c

	Instructions for clang:

		CC=clang ./configure --prefix=/home/$USER/buildarea
		CC=clang make && make install
		/home/$USER/buildarea/bin/clang-wrap hello.c

TESTING:
--------

	To download, build and run the hlibc-test test suite invoke:

		make gcctest|clangtest


